caption: This is my favorite place for Vietnamese food. I typically order the Chicken Pho and the Shrimp rolls and everything is delicious. The customer service is always excellent. Highly recommended!
Nice people, but honestly this was the worst PHO I've ever had. And the shrimp in the summer rolls weren't fresh and were brown.
Good food but not outstanding. The ample size of the condiments is a plus.
First visit. Put my go to spot to shame. Huge portions. Polite staff.
Great food and friendly people. I will definitely be coming back again.
Chicken rolls were good but I can't say the same thing for the pho. Broth wasn't as delicious as it should have been in a well-made pho. So, I'd say pho was meh.
Great place for quality Vietnamese food. It's so delicious. I had a cousin come into town and asked me to take him back here. This place has an awesome feel to it.
Amazing Pho
Their shrimp and crab fried rice is sooo damn good! Really worth the price 😊

What is the point of me having to order at the door if you're going to make my drink with no gloves and mask and also cup your bare hands over the top of my drink without it's lid. Gross. Use common sense
Delicious! Great portion sizes, fast service, and thoughtful staff. Beautiful presentation. Definitely coming back.

This place is amazing! People are not kidding when they call this the best pho in Baltimore. Get the shrimp and pork pho with those beef rolls! I didn’t think I would like them, but I tried them because of the reviews on here… I don’t regret a thing! I also got the shrimp summer rolls because I thought that I would like them more… The beef was better. The shrimp was good too, but the beef was really good. And I don’t even usually like summer rolls when they’re not fried. So that just goes to show you. Anyway, these reviews are real so whatever people recommend I would say go for it. The flavorful broth is amazing. I’m not going anywhere else for Vietnamese food it’s settled. Oh, and, the guy who answered the phone for my take-out order was really sweet. Great service is the cherry on top at this place

AMAZING. Best summer rolls i have ever had. The pho was amazing too. Love the broth. Only complaint is the pho tai advertises rare steak and the steak seemed to be well done. Other than that it was great.
I had an amazing experience recently. Best summer rolls I've had in a long time!

Hands down my favorite pho spot. The broth is consistently flavorful and the meat is tender. I never use the hoisin and sriracha because it’s not necessary. Just squeeze in a little lime juice and dig in. I haven’t explored the menu so I can only speak for the chicken pho, pork pho, and the rolls (his peanut sauce is fire).
The pho is well seasoned & huge, with plenty of meat and sprouts/lime/garnishes. For takeaway everything was packed really nicely too. I’ll definitely be going back!
The food is always fresh and delicious. Family owned and the seafood soup is AMAZING
The most delicious Pho' in Baltimore hands down.
4.28.20 THEY ARE OPEN FOR BUSINESS! CALL IN FOR PICKUP!

I'm amazed that I had the best tasting meal of my week's vacation in a food court. The pho, one of my favorite dishes, was among the best that I've ever had anywhere. I chose the pork and shrimp version. The portions of shrimp and pork were generous; I also believe that I got many more noodles than is normally the case. The broth was rich and tasty. My spouse was also enthusiastic about her seafood version. Service was prompt. I'll accept the somewhat dreary ambiance of this food court for such an excellent culinary experience.
REALLY enjoyed the Seafood pho! Lots of everything was in it.
Hands down best pho I have had. I have to go really out of my way to eat here.

Their food is is good, specially their spring rolls. Their Pho is really good and they have this crab and shrimp rice, OMGOSH it is sooo good. And the portions is good for 2. The owner is such a delight to talk to. I love going there for lunch when I have a craving.
An amazing amount of food, with taste that's even better for a good price.
Located in food court w/other vendors. Good size portions in spicy sauce. Customer service a bit lacking.
H2. Seafood Soup. Best Thing I've Ever Tasted. Thanks Leo. Thanks for being consistently awesome.

I went to this place twice. Once was ay the pizza place and the other was at a Sub place. Both places were nice. Customer Service was nice as well. The building was clean, inviting and music was playing. Over all it is a nice place to go and sit to eat. I enjoyed the atmosphere. In addition to, I felt comfortable while sitting eating lunch. And guess what No one was pan handling inside or outside of this place of this establishment when I went on both occassions.
username: I AM ALL WOMAN CEO Larissa Henderson

caption: I’m Vietnamese and I grew up with my mom’s version of home cooked pho and the deliciousness in this broth is the closest I have come to encounter authentic Vietnamese cuisine in Baltimore. Service is friendly and fast. Food court setting is casual. Prices are reasonable. They now take credit card too!
Absolutely DELICIOUS.....Had the beef Pho added shrimp... The broth was delicious and huge portions... The summer rolls are scrumptious as well. Great Customer Service.

They now accept credit. Heads up if you don’t finish your food, they make you pay for to go containers for your soup. 32oz $1, 16oz .50  Let me start off saying they’re going extremely friendly and pleasant. They work quickly but the food still comes out so hot and fresh. They give you SO MUCH meat and food. So much fresh veggies and delicious broth.  I ordered the pho # 3 with the Flank and Rare beef. CHUNKS of fresh, moist meat. Not dry whatsoever! I found this place based on a frequents recommendation who works close by, I live across town. Unless you work close by and walk here, street parking can be a little tricky. Just be patient and search the surrounding streets for meter parking. ITS WORTH it! I will absolutely be back and bring all my friends.
Great tasting spring rolls and the Pho soup hit the spot on a good Saturday afternoon!😎😎😎
Eat here!!!!!! It is amazing. Not a fancy place, don’t expect that but expect authentic awesome food.

Best pho place in Baltimore!!! The P5 is the best, actual tendon it’s sooo yummy!! The owner and his family are super nice and now they have electronic payments so I don’t have to go to the atm across the street!!
Love this place.
Delicious.

Absolutely hands down the best pho I’ve ever laid my tastebuds on. Even if you’re not vegan, try the V10. Don’t bother with an appetizer. You won’t have room. Cash only and discreet BYOB. Atmosphere is cafeteria style, but still...
Food Was Very Good!!

I love this place I have been coming here for over a year now and I always order the same thing 😋 the seafood pho it's sooo good it got lump crab meat,tiny scallops and shrimp is freshly made and it taste and smells so delicious. Family own and the customer service is top notch. The only down for me is that is cash only. Keep up the great work you guys.
Food is great and the service is good
Best phõ in Baltimore. We also love the shrimp and garlic fried rice.
Awesome awesome awesome! Priced well too!
A+
Cash ONLY, AUTHENTIC TASTE IN ABUNDANCY.  THE CUSTOMER SERVICE WAS EXCEPTIONAL.

Great bowl of pho, especially for the price. I would definitely come back. The broth was slightly sweet, which was unique, but it went from an 8/10 to 10/10 with just a little sirracha to give it a savory, spicy, sweet balance. They give you so much meat too. The flank tastes amazing.
Good solid portions! There’s a lot of noodles and meat and plenty of topping to customize your pho. The broth wasn’t as flavorful as I thought and the meat was tough. Definitely had better
Delicious pho and cheap the portions is huge, I wish they have a half of portion with a half of price
Pho ga, shrimp summer rolls... always good
One of the best Vietnam restaurant in Baltimore
I've had both the beef and seafood pho. Both are great with plenty of noodles and meat. The seafood pictured below really hit the spot. I added sriracha to the soup for and extra kick on a cold day.
Best Pho in the city. Just wish there was an option for delivery.
Best place for pho. 10/10
Ample portions and excellent variety of dishes to sample! Soup seems to be by far the most popular item.
Amazing noodle bowls!!
The food is amazing, the staff are friendly, and they have pho that is already gluten free (and perhaps the best in the city).  Love this pho!!
Not that great. The Pho has a strange hint of cinnamon.
I go out of my way for this place.

Having tried every pho place in the Bmore area, this is hands down the best overall. The beef broth does have the essence of cardamom or anise, can’t really decipher that may not be for everyone. But personally, I think it adds a tremendous amount of flavor. The meat is consistently just right. Also, the hi tieu with pork is to die for! Pork is perfectly tender and the garlic adds a thrilling punch.
Cool
Good beef stock and portions. Try d veggies tofu pho if u like vegetables. The only drawback is it's located inside an uninviting food court.

We went for lunch and shared an order of pork rolls and each had a bowl of Pho. Both the rolls and the soup had twice as much meat as most Pho restaurants I have eaten in. The broth was good and had traditional spices and was not over salty. It was a bit hard to find, you have to walk up some stairs to get to the food court entrance. Don’t be put off by it being in a food court, the food was good and generous portions !

Can't say enough good things about this place.  If you love Vietnamese food and are near downtown Baltimore, don't pass up Mekong Delta.  Call first, occasionally closed when owners go on vacation.  Currently closed until September 4, 2018.

Most of the places inside this plaza are closed. I had my heart set on Vietnamese pho and the place was closed until further notice. I purchased food from the fresh market there, it was good but a little pricy for lunch.
This is the best pho I have ever had.  Leo makes it differently than anyone else.
BEST PHO in Bmore! Everything here is delicious!
The food was delicious the atmosphere was terrific 😍
Fantastic viet noodle soup, really tasty.
Phenomenal food and large portions! Don't let the foodcourt-que location turn you away. This place is amazing. The noodles are cooked when you order and service is still quick.
Not as good as it used to be. The customer service is rough.
every time after ate their pho my body got  inflamed such as sore throat, toothache, stay away this place, god knows what kind of ingredients in their artificial taste broth.
Definitely a good bang-for-buck establishment for lunch.

The food is good, and they give you a lot for your money, however I have one huge complaint when it comes to lunch.  Maybe I'm crazy, but when I order lunch to go, I want to be able to eat it.  They give you too much broth, too many noodles and sprouts, and you can't eat it unless you have a giant bowl to put it in.  Make the portions smaller and put it all together, I want to eat my food for lunch, not play restaurateur at my desk.  The spring rolls are large and full of flavor, I filled up on those and had to take my "lunch" home to eat--reheated--for dinner with my partner.  This is the reason I don't order Indian food for lunch, you get too much in too many containers, now I know not to go here for lunch...

This is sub par pho. Also note worthy; they tried not to give me a cup of water and insisted on me buying a bottle. I said you have to give me a cup for water and gave me some washed out cup and said go to the water fountain. Then when I asked for a to go container I was charged a dollar. This place is not worth your money
The phu here is really good. Great to grab for lunch or dinner. Very good quality meat.
Food is great, bad customer service.
Awesome summer rolls & fried rice

Pho !!! Delicious, fresh, deeply flavourful broth in my tendon & rare beef pho. I love this Vietnamese soup, and Mekong Delta Café on Charles Street in Baltimore does a particularly good rendition. Slight negative (for me): broth was a bit sweeter than i like. But I'd definitely go here again.
YES. GO.

I come back a couple of times per month. Great pho with huge portions. Owners are also super friendly. Only downside is that it's a cash only place.  My vegetarian friend also likes their veggie pho, and when she ordered that they actually asked if she could eat beef broth, which we appreciated as some pho places will just use beef broth and give you pho with vegetables and pass that off as vegetarian.
Overrated. The chicken in the summer roll is very dry. Pho soup is nice but beef is over cook
It's small locally owned place by a cute Asian couple. Very friendly! The sandwiches are delicious and made in front of you

The food is good but customer service is lacking. They take almost 25 minutes for vegetarian orders. Today he didn't even take my order before advising that it's 20 minutes wait for anything vegetarian. I don't anticipate me going back anytime soon.

Just tried today. The Summer rolls are good, rice is OK, but pho noodle is not that good. The bottom line is they are very affordable and worth to give it try. By the way, there are a lot of meat in pho.
Best pho in Baltimore.
Wonderful noodle soup

THE place to get pho in Baltimore. Sure, there's more places now than when Mekong Delta started, but they still reign supreme. The beef broth is rich, complex, and tastes like love. Don't be shy - get it with tendon and enjoy some melt-in-your-mouth umami. I will forever mourn the removal of the crepe from the menu, but I will belly up with my cash for the tendon pho till Mekong Delta's last day.
Best Vietnam food in Baltimore. Family run and very friendly.

Excellent, huge bowls of Pho. This place is cash only so remember to hit the ATM on your way over. Very popular during lunch hours. Sometimes there can be a very long wait. But if you're a local or working late they stay open until dinner time.
unique flavors
Best pho in Baltimore without question. Flavors, spicy level, temps and toppings are all on point. I like the beef. The monster sized spring and summer rolls are great too.
Unbelievable that this place is in a food court but it ROCKS!!! My pho was (yep) Phò-nominal!!!

Mi favorite Vietnamese restaurant in Baltimore (and the world). Probably even better than eating in Vietnam. I have been in the south east of Asia several times, and the food here is, for my taste and standards, better than eating there. Clean, healthy, and friendly service. Highly recommended.
Great broth, best pho I've had in Baltimore.
Most flavorful Pho broth I've ever had. The proprietor is always friendly and accommodating.
They just stuff everything into such a small bowl of soup. You get no room to put some fresh sprouts, etc. I like the fact that you don't have to pay any tips. But it's cash only.

The best bowl of soup in the region portions are smaller than traditional pho restaurants but that’s made up in the over all flavor and ingredients. Giant sized summer rolls that are great to share or a meal on their own!

The pho is real good, tendon is perfect. Pho might be a little sweeter than traditional but im not an athority, its just sweeter than other places ive been. Asian food this good at this price is really rare in baltimore this spot is awesome
Delicious and very friendly service
Excellent food. Food court not as comfortable as the previous restaurant.
I found out that they are closed to the end of August 2016. I was really looking forward to it.
Cinnamony, but delicious. So delicious.
I didn't like the Orange chicken.  Too sweet.
A gem in Baltimore.   Best pho !
Delicious bowl of pho. A hidden treasure in Baltimore
Always great! ^^
Best broth in the Baltimore area!
While the setting is not appealing, the pho (and other soups) here is excellent. Note that this is a cash-only establishment.
Best pho Ive ever had..
I always get pho. It's always amazing. Definitely made with love. The serving is huge, I can never finish it all and the price is cheap. They could totally get away with charging more.
The grilled tofu and my Pho were amazing yesterday. Already trying to plan my next visit there.
I've had pho at numerous places throughout the Baltimore/DC area. This is by far the best pho I've ever had. Excellent broth, very flavorful.
Do not go here. Take my advice, they have terrible broth, they are cheap, and it blows. Good day

Mekong Delta Rocks!! That's all you really need to know. I've tasted and enjoyed many other traditional Vietnamese restaurants, this place hits a home run every time.  Their broths are spot on and their service , great.  Come try it and see for yourself.

The new Mekong Delta location is in that weird food mall to the east of the Charles Towers. It has the ambiance of eating in a bus station and is still cash only. That aside, their soup broths are still among the most flavorful and interesting in town, second only to Saigon Remembered (now in Cockeysville). Summer rolls are delicious and giant, like 6" each. Split the beef and lemongrass summer roll order with a friend and that would have been plenty for lunch for both of us. I'd go there if I happened to be in the neighborhood again.
Best pho in Baltimore. They only accept cash, and sell bottled water only.
